The general accidental release prevention program and chemical-specific prevention steps [40 CFR 68.155(c)]:
Calumet is not required to implement the Program Level 3 prevention program requirements under the RMP regulations because they are eligible for RMP Program Level 1. However, protecting the environment and the safety and health of employees, customers, contractors, communities, and the public is fundamental to the way Calumet conducts its business. To integrate environmental, safety, and health management into business activities, Calumet will:

1.	Pursue excellence in the design, construction, operation, and restoration of all properties and facilities;
2.	Be a responsible steward of all products and services;
3.	Train and prepare employees for emergencies and other contingencies;
4.	Communicate openly regarding business activities;
5.	Assign clear responsibilities to all employees and contractors;
6.	Provide employees with resources and training to meet assigned responsibilities;
7.	Assess the potential risks of business activities;
8.	Comply with all applicable laws and regulations;
9.	Participate in the development of new laws, regulations, and technologies;
10.	Review performance and communicate progress; and
11.	Expect continuous improvement.

The facility stores Oleum in an aboveground storage tank. Mitigation measures to control the release include a concrete dike six feet in height that would be capable of containing more than 100% of the volume of the storage tank. Further, the tank is located approximately in the geographic center of the Calumet facility (not at the property border).

